Due to the complexity of compositions, FT-IR data were further applied. As shown in Fig. 3
                     , the peaks at 2868, 2720, 1732, 1465, 1298, 1250 and 1114cm−1 observed in poly(UA-co-PEGMA), which can be attributed to CH2, CO (HCO), CO (COOH), σ as (CH2
                     ), CO (COO), CO (COOH), CO (COC), respectively. After introducing dopamine and PEI, the peak in 2720cm−1 disappeared, suggesting that aldehyde group involved in the reaction of MALI. In addition, the peaks near 1600cm−1 were appeared in polymer-FONs, which may be from NH and CH in benzene ring. The peak at 1110cm−1 evidently changed stronger than poly(UA-co-PEGMA), and it can be assigned to the CN in PEI. Therefore, all of the above results indicated that polymer-FONs have been successfully synthesized.
